<title type="html"><![CDATA[My TLROM hack crashes. Why?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10874&amp;p=123608#p123608"><![CDATA[
Hi everyone!<br /><br />I've been lurking for a few months, learning a ton, but this is my first post. <br /><br />Yesterday I put my first hacked NES game on an UNROM PCB. It works perfectly. <br /><br />Tonight I tried something a little more complex and put a hack on a TLROM. It is a hack of Double Dragon III. The one that makes it easier to play. I got it all soldered together using the correct (I think) EPROMS (27c010) and wiring changes. Unfortunately, when I play it, it crashes after a few minutes into the game play. The screen scrambles, freezes, and the music stutters.<br /><br />I've double and triple checked all of my connections with a multimeter. The game plays fine on an emulator. I'm confident that I split the ROM correctly. The EPROMs burned and verified without errors.<br /><br />What could I have done wrong?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6335">Dinosaur</a> — Fri Jan 10, 2014 7:52 pm</p><hr />
